The death has occurred of an entrepreneur, a patriot and an international businessman, Dr. Olabode Thompson Mobolaji Kalejaye. Born into the family of the late Pa Emeda and Mama Biliya Aduke Kalejaiye on January 20, 1956, Olabode died on December 31, 2020. He was 64. After his Higher School Certificate (HSC) at Baptist Academy, Obanikoro, Lagos, Kalejaiye had a brief stint in Journalism, working with The Punch and the defunct National Concord. At the same time, he pursued his professional studies in Accountancy before travelling to England in 1981 for further study. It was during this time that he met his wife and they got married in 1985. On his return to Nigeria in 1987, he set up his consultancy business, currently under the umbrella of Harvest Investments Company Ltd. He was a member of the Board of Directors of the now defunct NAL Merchant Bank, and a member of Economic and Security Advisory Team for the Federal Government. He was a devout Christian and was the Senior Pastor of ShepherdHouse Church, which he founded with his wife in 2008. Kalejaiye is survived by his wife of 35 years, Olabisi, three children, Tinuola, Oluwatomi and Olabode jr, grandchildren, siblings, cousins, nephews and nieces.  